~ about_living_here

Maria: [#explaining] This isn't my house. Not really.
Maria: [#matter-of-fact] Mommy brought me here one day. She said we had to hide.

- Hide from what?
	Maria: [#uncertain] I don't know. She was crying a lot.
	Maria: [#remembering] There were people saying mean things. Outside our real house.
	Maria: [#confused] They were angry at Mommy. And at me. I don't really understand.
	Maria: [#innocent] Mommy said my eyes look like Papa's. Blue like the sky.
	=> about_hiding
- Where is your real house?
	Maria: [#vague] I... I can't remember. [wait=0.3]It's one of the fuzzy things.
	Maria: [#frustrated] I remember the garden though. Mommy's flowers. She likes the purple ones ones.
	Maria: [#wistful] And I remember the sound of boots. Soldiers walking past our window.
	=> main_menu

~ about_hiding

Maria: [#sad] Mommy said we'd stay here just a little while. Until things got better.
Maria: [#remembering] She kept looking at the door. Like she was waiting for someone.
Maria: [#childlike] I asked if Papa was coming. She didn't answer.
Maria: [#innocent] And then... [wait=0.5]I got sleepy. Very sleepy.
Maria: [#confused] And when I woke up, Mommy was gone. And everything feels... different now.

- Different how?
	Maria: [#struggling] Like... like I'm here but not here. Does that make sense?
	Maria: [#ghostly] Sometimes I can touch things. Sometimes my hand goes through.
	Maria: [#accepting] But I've learned to manage.
	=> main_menu
- I think I understand
	=> main_menu

~ about_parents

Maria: [#simple] Mommy and Daddy is... [wait=0.5]I don't know where they are.

- Why not?
	Maria: [#innocent] Papa had to stay at the garrison. With the other soldiers.
	Maria: [#explaining] But he would visit sometimes. Bring food. And cloth from the ship.
	Maria: [#uncertain] Mommy would get quiet when he came. But she'd smile. A tired smile.
	Maria: [#childlike] I think she was happy for the food.
	=> about_parents_relationship
- Do you miss them?
	Maria: [#honest] I miss Mommy. [wait=0.3]I don't remember Papa enough to miss him.
	Maria: [#wistful] But sometimes I wish I had a papa like other children. One who lived at home.
	=> main_menu

~ about_parents_relationship

- Did your parents love each other?
	Maria: [#thoughtful] *tilts head* I don't know. [wait=0.3]I never saw them hold hands.
	Maria: [#remembering] Papa would give Mommy things. And she would thank him. Very polite.
	Maria: [#innocent] Like when you thank someone for helping you carry water.
	=> about_papa_more
- What was their relationship like?
	Maria: [#describing] Papa would come. Mommy would serve him food. He would eat.
	Maria: [#observing] Sometimes he'd pat my head.
	Maria: [#matter-of-fact] Then he'd leave. And Mommy would count the coins he left.
	Maria: [#childlike] She always looked relieved when he came. But also... sad.
	=> about_papa_more

~ about_papa_more

- What do you remember about your Papa?
	Maria: [#vague] He was tall. And his uniform was always clean. Shiny buttons.
	Maria: [#remembering] His hands were big. Rough. He'd ruffle my hair sometimes.
	Maria: [#uncertain] And his eyes were blue. Like mine. People would stare at my eyes.
	Maria: [#innocent] Mommy said I was lucky. That Papa's visits meant we had food.
